{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We found that CarD-T trained on data subset for 60% of G1 and 2A carcinogens was able to correctly identify 100% of G1 & G2A class carcinogens from the full Context Training -DS.",
    "Thus, we constrained the training set to 60% of the IARC G1 and 2A entities to account for the least over-fitting 54.",
    "This selection process engendered a corpus comprising a total of 11,985 annotated text (including expanded sentences and synthetic sentences) for training.",
    "The remaining 40% of IARC G1 and 2A entities were consistently recognized in our validation set of 7,990 sentence corpus.",
    "Next, we applied the CarD-T NER to annotate entities in the 216,721 remaining carcinogen abstracts from DS-Carcinogen."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
